    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Excellent watch with many features
    Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2025
    Color: gray
    I honestly wasn’t sure whether or not to believe the glowing reviews for this watch, but it really is great. I was skeptical about a device this low priced giving accurate oximeter measurements - but it does! I’ve only had it a short while, but out of the box, it feels and... See more
    I honestly wasn’t sure whether or not to believe the glowing reviews for this watch, but it really is great. I was skeptical about a device this low priced giving accurate oximeter measurements - but it does! I’ve only had it a short while, but out of the box, it feels and works like a high quality gadget.
    The first thing I actually noticed was the feel of the band - it feels like they put thought in to it and made with high quality material. It doesn’t have a funky clasp like the ones on Apple Watches, you can adjust it so the watch feels just right on your wrist. The watch itself has a good weight to it as well. When you balance it in your hand it has a substantial weight to it.
    Probably the most novel thing to me is the way the charging cable connects to the watch. The USB end is the typical end that you always plug in the wrong way, switch around and then switch back because you had it right the first time, but the end that connects to the watch is magnetic and it just jumps right into place on the watch! You align the connector and put them next to each other and, “click,” done.
    This is one time when you get what you pay for and more.

    I love smart gadgets. I exercise, and anything that tracks my heart rate and distances is gold to me. Plus I just like wearing a watch, it's always more convenient than dragging my phone out of my pocket. I had one already but it stopped charging properly, so I kept my eyes open for an upgrade. When I saw this one I decided to try it.

    This is a nice tracker! The band is comfortable and easily adjustable. The heart rate monitor seems pretty accurate against my other monitors. The distance tracker was within 0.2 miles off on a three mile walk compared to my phone, and I consider this to be excellent as far as accuracy.

    Overall I'm pleased with this tracker. It works well, tracks a lot of information, and is inexpensive enough that I won't be too angry if it's lost or broken.

  • JEFF
    5.0 out of 5 starsAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product
    Fitness Tracker
    Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2024
    Color: BLUE
    In my opinion, the size is about ideal; it is not too cumbersome, yet it is big enough that one can see the details without having to squint. Both the brightness and the resolution are remarkable, which makes it simple to see the information even when it is brightly lit.... See more
    In my opinion, the size is about ideal; it is not too cumbersome, yet it is big enough that one can see the details without having to squint. Both the brightness and the resolution are remarkable, which makes it simple to see the information even when it is brightly lit. However, this particular wristwatch finds an excellent mix between size and visibility, in contrast to other smartwatches that I have used in the past that had displays that were either too tiny or not bright enough. The user interface is easy to understand, and switching between functions is logical and unobtrusive. The aspects of this watch that are dedicated to monitoring one's health are fairly extensive. Daily monitoring of my heart rate, SpO2 levels, and sleep patterns was accomplished with the help of this gadget. I find the continuous heart rate monitor to be quite useful since it enables me to measure the amount of stress that I am experiencing simultaneously throughout my exercises and during my workplace. Particularly during the high-altitude climbs that I went on not too long ago, the SpO2 function was a wonderful addition since it provided me with information about how my body was adjusting to the higher altitude. Managing my exercise objectives and my overall well-being is made easier by the fact that these measurements provide me with more information about my overall health, which I believe is beneficial.
